%p
  %strong
    Q:
  %i
    How is testing different from the last season with the IQA?
  %br
  %strong
    A:
  The IRDP has completely revamped the internal structure of the written tests. The new system more effectively tests candidates on their knowledge of specific rules, and follows a question format that will allow for easier understanding. In addition, the field test has been streamlined, as well as a sixth section that has been added to test a candidate's ability to make the correct calls in a game. Additionally, it's all offered through one convenient, automated site (this one). 
